duties_responsibilities.duty: Acquire extensive knowledge of Medicaid policy and procedures to make timely and accurate Medicaid eligibility determinations.
Provide eligibility assistance to members and applicants in various formats including electronic, mail, email, in person, or phone.
Work in a call-center format, involving a combination of sedentary work on a computer and assisting members by phone.
Independently work, perform routine activities, and pay attention to deadlines.
Mastery of eligibility policy and procedure for potential career growth in the health insurance field.

education_certification.credential: Baccalaureate degree in any field (health-related field preferred)
